result.execSummary:
The defendant Susan J Fullerton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Susan J Fullerton was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Susan J Fullerton is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Susan J Fullerton was found guilty of Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (5th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Jury brought in at 9:03, Clerk swears jury. Court reads opening jury instructions. Opening instructions by ADA Cardona at 9:15. Opening instructions by Atty. Breun at 9:22 State calls witness, sworn, takes stand. Direct exam by ADA Cardona. Cross exam by Atty. Breun. Re-direct by ADA Cardona. Witness excused. State calls witness, sworn, takes stand. Direct exam by ADA Cardona. Witness has identified defendant. Jury excused at 10:01 to hear refusal part. Marked exhibit 1, offered and received. Cross exam by Atty. Breun. Redirect by ADA Cardona. Re-cross by Atty. Breun. State wants to use the refusal, Atty. Breun objects.  Court rules, allowing it. Jury back in at 10:32. ADA Cardona continues direct exam. Marked exhibit 2, offered and received. Cross exam by Atty. Breun. Re-direct by ADA Cardona. Witness is excused, but not released from subpoena. State calls witness, sworn, takes stand. Direct exam by ADA Cardona. Witness identifies defendant. Cross exam by Atty. Breun. Re-direct by ADA Cardona. Witness is excused, but not released from subpoena. State calls witness, sworn, takes stand. Direct exam by ADA Cardona. Marked exhibit 3, offered and received. Cross exam by Atty. Breun. Re-direct by ADA Cardona. Witness excused, released from subpoena. Lunch break at 11:59, to return at 1:00. Back on record at 1:13. State was informed that the Analyst and an Officer were talking in the hallway, a witness on the Defense overheard the conversation. Court calls the Analyst, sworn, Court asks what the discussion was.  Court calls witness, sworn, takes stand.  Atty. Breun does direct exam on what he heard in the hallway between the analyst and the police officers. Witness is no longer able to testify.  He is released from subpoena. Atty. Breun motions the court for a mistrial, Court denies the motion.  Jury back in at 1:32. State calls Russel Schafer, sworn, takes stand
Direct exam by ADA Cardona. Witness identifies defendant. Witness is excused, released from subpoena. State calls witness, sworn, takes stand. Direct exam by ADA Cardona. Marked exhibit 4, offered and received. Cross exam by Atty. Breun. Re-direct by ADA Cardona. Witness excused, but not released from subpoena. State rests at 2:22. Atty. Breun calls witness, sworn, takes stand. Direct exam by Atty. Breun. Cross exam by ADA Cardona. Re-direct by Atty. Breun. Witness is excused, released from subpoena. Atty. Breun calls witness, sworn, takes stand. Direct exam by Atty. Breun. Marked exhibit 5, offered and received. Marked exhibit 6. Cross exam by ADA Cardona. Break, jurors excused at 3:35
Court has colloquy with defendant about her right to testify or not to testify.  After discussion, defendant will testify. Went over jury instructions. Jury brought in at 4:07. Cross exam continues by ADA Cardona. Re-direct by Atty. Breun. Re-cross by ADA Cardona. Witness excused. Atty. Breun calls defendant, sworn, and takes stand. Direct exam by Atty. Breun. Cross exam by ADA Cardona. Re-direct by Atty. Breun. Defendant excused from the stand. State re-calls witness. Direct exam by ADA Cardona. No cross exam. Witness excused. No further witnesses. Court instructs jury at 4:40 PM. Closing arguments. Alternate juror J.R. selected and excused at 5:31 PM. Court provides closing instructions to jury. Bailiff sworn 
Jury excused for deliberation at 5:35 PM. Discussion with counsel re: exhibits, counsel agree jury may review exhibits 1-4 if requested. Bailiff informed Court that verdict reached 6:10 pm. Jury brought in at 6:22 pm. Verdict- Ct 1- Not Guilty. Verdict- Ct 2- Guilty. Atty. Breun requested jury poll. Jury polled. Jury released at 6:24 pm. State moved for decision on verdict. Defense moved for judgment not withstanding the verdict . Court entered judgment as rendered by jury, bail revoked
State requested a PSI; Atty. Breun would rather do a sentencing w/out a PSI ASAP. Counsel agree to sentencing tomorrow August 31, 2016 at 1:00 PM. Accompanying TR cases will track.
